    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go to the List of Blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the Categories block to display the posts&#8217; categories. This block is primarily nested inside a<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/query-loop-block/\"> query loop</a> block and helps to customize the appearance of the query loop.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a Categories block, click the <strong>Block Inserter</strong> icon when editing the page template. Search for the Categories<strong> block</strong>. Click on it to add the block to your page template.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/adding-category-block.mp4\"></video><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Video showing how to add Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also type /categories and hit enter in a new paragraph block to add the Categories block quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"437\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/categories-block-1024x437.png\" alt=\"Image showing how to add Categories block with the slash inserter.\" class=\"wp-image-16357371\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/categories-block-1024x437.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/categories-block-300x128.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/categories-block-768x328.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/06/categories-block.png 1218w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">How to add Categories block quickly</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To view the block toolbar, click on the block and the toolbar will be displayed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block comes with unique toolbar icons. These block-specific controls allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Categories block shows five buttons in the block toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Drag icon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Move arrows</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change text alignment</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3WV4UeF9OMEU_NKd_leRXDGqPy9ulVgkCcN1XIRa8KbA4Bz1_xnc_mEBFs5CmlHrwLwTgnnUz3BhRKfMS-sxJsq4LPZOI6AAmHNWCA2z_PlG17ouwxT56p9k3xELCYUvjSfku6bj\" alt=\"Categories block toolbar\" style=\"width:328px;height:86px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Categories block toolbar</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Transform to:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"372\" height=\"405\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-transforms.png\" alt=\"Transform options in Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365606\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-transforms.png 372w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-transforms-276x300.png 276w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 372px) 100vw, 372px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Transform options in Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the \u201cTransform\u201d button to convert the Categories block into&nbsp;<strong>Tags, Columns, Details</strong>, or a&nbsp;<strong>Group</strong>&nbsp;block:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Group</strong>: Place the block inside a Group to apply shared styles like background color, padding, or borders around the entire section.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tags</strong>: Switch to display a tag list instead of categories, useful for showcasing post tags in a similar layout.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Columns</strong>: Use columns to organize categories into multiple vertical sections, enhancing visual structure.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Details</strong>: Wrap the category list in an expandable/collapsible container to save space and improve readability.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Drag icon:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/LOeUP5AIHfAVcf3TJ48liWDB9P3l3HFu-rcuhFCvMx45GbaO5ffRRdFG_Q8Dx1go4uUH9dvwgAtOJCBcB7IfOp0dJ7SiutLyWu3cg2Fzzjhbq92NEHVuXtIvsEdBYSkp-sW91FtU\" alt=\"Drag icon in the Categories block\" style=\"width:298px;height:78px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Drag icon in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the rectangle of dots, then drag to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Move arrows:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/lgn3n_EG2vlBv_qwEck8d1VwrvP6k2N3bDpvfzgUk4-4FnefAFae6zUyhQAvN10qZ5vR7RZb4KtNAEDuYYUv5DM_qWuvCZFMx9NckyfXqocD7pInnEEfWasN83XTTDPms1qKwc2w\" alt=\"Move arrows in the Categories block\" style=\"width:324px;height:85px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Move arrows in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to move the block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change text alignment</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/JsIE08dBZF7XXtboBBffzuApeuJsY5W-Gk-_8kDve2NY0FQupCXlYCzWh_3_OYNk_eFMoZPa73Rd8QFDJ36ZKbhZLiGMPuoWEyCWUbO076kaWEumQG2TlQvIOm80Q4hEUTg46SAR\" alt=\"Change text alignment in Categories block\" style=\"width:209px;height:244px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Change text alignment in Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the \u201cChange alignment\u201d button in the Block toolbar to display the alignment drop-down. You can align the block text to the left, make it center-aligned or align it to the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">More options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the block toolbar, every block has specific options in the editor sidebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>If you do not see the sidebar, click the icon next to the Publish button.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"402\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/How-to-turn-on-the-Block-Settings-sidebar-402x1024.png\" alt=\"How to turn on the Block Settings sidebar\" class=\"wp-image-16365770\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/How-to-turn-on-the-Block-Settings-sidebar-402x1024.png 402w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/How-to-turn-on-the-Block-Settings-sidebar-118x300.png 118w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/How-to-turn-on-the-Block-Settings-sidebar.png 540w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">How to turn on the Block Settings sidebar</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"538\" height=\"710\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Categories-block-settings.png\" alt=\"Categories block settings\" class=\"wp-image-16365776\" style=\"width:274px;height:373px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Categories-block-settings.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Categories-block-settings-227x300.png 227w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Categories block settings</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Styles</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can customize \u201cStyles\u201d options to change the appearance of the Categories block. Available options are <strong>Default </strong>or<strong> Pilled shaped</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Default</strong>: Displays the categories in a standard list format, following the theme\u2019s typography and spacing.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pilled shaped:</strong> Displays each category inside a rounded pill-like container, making them stand out with a more modern and visually distinct look.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"538\" height=\"242\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Change-the-style-of-display-categories.png\" alt=\"Styles settings in the Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365772\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Change-the-style-of-display-categories.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Change-the-style-of-display-categories-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Change the style of display categories</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Color </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can customize the text color, background color, gradient background, and link color for the Categories block.<em> The color options available will vary based on the theme.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"553\" height=\"391\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-color.png\" alt=\"Color settings in the Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365604\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-color.png 553w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-color-300x212.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Color settings in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">See this guide for more information about changing colors.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Typography </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>On this tab, you can adjust properties such as the Size, Font, Appearance, Line height, Letter spacing, Decoration and Letter case.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To access all the typography options click on the + button in the right corner of the Typography tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"553\" height=\"415\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-typography.png\" alt=\"Typography settings in the Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365607\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-typography.png 553w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-typography-300x225.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 553px) 100vw, 553px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Typography settings in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/typography-settings-overview/\">Get more details about changing typography settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Dimensions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>On this tab, you can adjust properties such as the <strong>Padding, Margin, and Block spacing</strong>\u00a0for the\u00a0<strong>Categories</strong>\u00a0block. These options help in defining the spacing around and between elements, ensuring proper alignment and layout consistency across different sections of your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"538\" height=\"610\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Dimensions-settings-in-the-Categories-block.png\" alt=\"Dimensions settings in the Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365774\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Dimensions-settings-in-the-Categories-block.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Dimensions-settings-in-the-Categories-block-265x300.png 265w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Dimensions settings in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Get more details about changing dimensions settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Border</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>On this tab, you can add <strong>custom border</strong>\u00a0to the\u00a0<strong>Categories</strong>\u00a0block by adjusting\u00a0<strong>Border width, Style, Color, and Radius</strong>. These options provide greater flexibility in styling, allowing you to create visually distinct category lists that align with your site&#8217;s design.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"538\" height=\"372\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Border-settings-in-the-Categories-block-1.png\" alt=\"Border settings in the Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365775\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Border-settings-in-the-Categories-block-1.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/Border-settings-in-the-Categories-block-1-300x207.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 538px) 100vw, 538px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Border settings in the Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/border-settings-overview/\">Get more details about changing border settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Advanced settings:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The \u201cAdvanced\u201d tab lets you enter character(s) that can be used to separate the category terms. The default setting is a comma.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add CSS class(es) to your block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles to the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"272\" height=\"289\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/03/categories-advanced.png\" alt=\"Advanced setting in Categories block\" class=\"wp-image-16365608\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced setting in Categories block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update 2025-06-05\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add border support</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add dimensions support</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add styles support</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update screenshots to 6.8.1</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update 2025-04-22 (props to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/karthickmurugan/\">@karthickmurugan</a>)\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add color support.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update screenshots to 6.8.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add missing ALT tags.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated on 2023-06-27\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Renamed &#8216;Post Categories Block&#8217; with &#8216;Categories Block&#8217;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated screenshots/video to 6.2.2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2022-03-21 </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
